The paper proposes a new Quality Diversity (QD) algorithm that combines techniques from Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy (CMA-ES) and mapping techniques for maintaining diversity in QD. The algorithm is evaluated on both standard continuous optimization benchmarks and the strategic game Hearthstone. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new algorithm for optimization and reinforcement learning. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on a game and uses techniques from CMA-ES, which is a popular optimization algorithm in machine learning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes an evolutionary algorithm for optimization. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the paper evaluates the algorithm on a strategic game. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper discusses the use of the algorithm for design and testing, which are relevant to control systems.
